1
00:00:02,370 --> 00:00:04,702
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> THE PRETENDER.    
        I KNOW THE TRUTH.       


2
00:00:04,772 --> 00:00:07,205
        AND WHAT TRUTH          
        IS THAT, JAROD?         


3
00:00:07,274 --> 00:00:10,342
    THE TRUTH...                
    ABOUT WHAT MAKES YOU SAD.   


4
00:00:10,411 --> 00:00:14,179
YOUR MOTHER WAS                 
A SPECIAL PERSON.               
    MY MOTHER WAS WEAK. PERIOD. 


5
00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:17,950
        THE ONLY THING THAT     
        EVER BOTHERED ME WAS:   
        WHY IN AN ELEVATOR?     


6
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:20,418
<i>YOUR MOTHER</i>                     
<i>WAS A VERY SPECIAL WOMAN.</i>       


7
00:00:20,487 --> 00:00:24,056
<i>THERE WAS A PART OF HER</i>         
<i>I KNEW BETTER THAN ANYONE.</i>      


8
00:00:24,125 --> 00:00:27,559
<i>THERE WAS A PART OF HER</i>         
<i>SHE KEPT HIDDEN, SEPARATE.</i>      


9
00:00:27,628 --> 00:00:30,895
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>IS THAT ALL YOU DO, JAROD?</i>      
<i>DIG UP THE PAST?</i>                


10
00:00:30,964 --> 00:00:34,032
    THAT'S EASY FOR YOU TO SAY. 
    YOU HAVE ONE.               


11
00:00:41,275 --> 00:00:43,976
[ Screaming ]                   
MAMA! MAMA!                     


12
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:45,911
THEY'RE TRYING TO HURT HER!     
        STAY HERE, JAROD.       


13
00:00:45,979 --> 00:00:48,580
        -<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>           
        - MAMA, NO!             


14
00:00:48,649 --> 00:00:50,014
        -<i> [ Gunshot ]</i>           
        -<i> NO!</i>                   


15
00:00:51,818 --> 00:00:53,752
            MAMA!               


16
00:00:53,821 --> 00:00:55,821
<i>[ Gunshot ]</i>                     


17
00:01:20,381 --> 00:01:22,381
<i>[ Phone Rings ]</i>                 


18
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:27,652
            WHAT?               
[ Sydney ]                      
WE'VE GOT A HIT.                


19
00:01:27,721 --> 00:01:30,722
JAROD'S THE FINEST SEWER RAT    
I'VE HAD THE PLEASURE TO        
WORK WITH.                      


20
00:01:30,790 --> 00:01:34,292
I'VE NEVER SEEN SOMEONE         
SO EXCITED ABOUT EXCREMENT      
IN MY LIFE.                     


21
00:01:34,361 --> 00:01:36,695
A REAL FECAL AFICIONADO.        


22
00:01:36,763 --> 00:01:38,797
                <i> [ Miss Parker ]</i>
                <i> HOW CHARMING.</i>  


23
00:01:38,866 --> 00:01:41,033
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>HOW LONG WAS JAROD HERE?</i>        
                COUPLE OF WEEKS.


24
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:44,236
        THAT'S ALL IT TOOK HIM  
        TO FIGURE IT OUT.       
<i>[ Miss Parker ] FIGURE WHAT OUT?</i>


25
00:01:44,305 --> 00:01:46,270
            THAT WE WERE DIGGING
            INTO AN AQUIFER.    


26
00:01:46,339 --> 00:01:48,773
    IF WE HAD HIT THAT THING,   
    IT WOULD'VE FLUSHED         
    45 MEMBERS...               


27
00:01:48,842 --> 00:01:50,942
OF THE INTERNATIONAL BROTHERHOOD
 OF SEWAGE WORKERS...           


28
00:01:51,011 --> 00:01:52,944
        RIGHT INTO              
        THE JAWS OF OBLIVION.   


29
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:56,548
JUST LIKE THAT EGYPTIAN ARMY    
IN<i> THE TEN COMMANDMENTS.</i>        
WHOOSH!                         


30
00:01:56,617 --> 00:01:59,084
            GREAT.              
            NOW JAROD IS MOSES. 


31
00:01:59,152 --> 00:02:01,086
                        MOSES?  


32
00:02:01,154 --> 00:02:04,156
CHARLTON HESTON.                
                [ Chuckles ]    
                RIGHT.          


33
00:02:09,229 --> 00:02:10,762
THANKS.                         


34
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:23,274
MR. McELROY,<i> THIS</i> IS WHERE      
JAROD ALWAYS EMERGED?           


35
00:02:23,343 --> 00:02:25,276
            RIGHT IN THIS SPOT. 


36
00:02:25,345 --> 00:02:27,612
    <i> SOMETHING SPECIAL ABOUT IT,</i>
    <i> BUT HE WOULDN'T TELL ME.</i>   


37
00:02:27,681 --> 00:02:29,847
    <i> SAID HE HAD TO SHIP OUT.</i>   


38
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:38,857
    <i> COMMANDER FORRESTER,</i>       
    <i> WE HAVE A SITUATION HERE.</i>  


39
00:02:38,926 --> 00:02:40,926
REPORT.                         
                    BOGEY, SIR. 


40
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:43,195
        VICTOR-CLASS SUBMARINE, 
        BEARING ONE FOUR EIGHT. 


41
00:02:43,263 --> 00:02:45,297
<i>[ Jarod ] AND CLOSING.</i>          


42
00:02:45,365 --> 00:02:48,032
THIS COULD BE THE ROGUE         
WE'RE LOOKING FOR.              


43
00:02:48,101 --> 00:02:51,269
RELAX, SAILOR.                  
THIS IS THE FUN PART.           


44
00:02:51,338 --> 00:02:53,839
    WHY DOES THE FUN PART       
    HAVE TO HAPPEN ON<i> MY</i> WATCH? 


45
00:02:53,907 --> 00:02:56,708
ALERT THE X.O.                  
AND THE CAPTAIN.                
                AYE, AYE, SIR.  


46
00:02:56,777 --> 00:02:58,777
            WE'VE GOT A FIGHT   
            ON OUR HANDS.       


47
00:03:01,248 --> 00:03:04,749
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


48
00:03:48,529 --> 00:03:51,296
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>ATTENTION ON DECK.</i>              
<i>[ Man #2 ] AS YOU WERE.</i>         


49
00:03:51,365 --> 00:03:53,498
<i>CAPTAIN NAGEL.</i>                  
<i>COMMANDER NASHTON.</i>              


50
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:55,500
IT'S THE<i> ROSTOV,</i> SIR.           


51
00:03:55,568 --> 00:03:57,735
    AFTER SHE DEPLOYED          
    FROM ODESSA,                


52
00:03:57,804 --> 00:04:01,306
<i>THE UZBEKI CAPTAIN</i>              
<i>DECLARED INDEPENDENCE</i>           
<i>FROM THE BLACK SEA FLEET.</i>       


53
00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:04,509
<i>HE'S ROGUE.</i>                     
WITH A HIP POCKET               
FULL OF NUCLEAR WARHEADS.       


54
00:04:04,578 --> 00:04:08,813
AND JUDGING FROM THE INTEL FILE,
HER FIRST STRIKE TARGET...      
IS LOS ANGELES.                 


55
00:04:08,882 --> 00:04:11,116
[ Beeping ]                     


56
00:04:11,185 --> 00:04:13,418
    - SOMETHING'S UP, SIRS.     
    - THEY'VE OPENED            
      THE V.L.S. DOORS.         


57
00:04:13,487 --> 00:04:16,187
THOSE S.L.B.M.'s WILL BE        
READY TO FIRE IN                
APPROXIMATELY TWO MINUTES.      


58
00:04:16,256 --> 00:04:20,258
        <i> TORPEDOES IN THE WATER,</i>
        <i> BEARING ONE THREE SEVEN</i>
        <i> AND ONE FOUR TWO.</i>      


59
00:04:20,327 --> 00:04:22,493
            READY TORPEDO DECOY.
READY DECOY.                    


60
00:04:22,562 --> 00:04:24,095
            READY DECOY. AYE.   


61
00:04:25,198 --> 00:04:27,599
        SOMETHING'S WRONG WITH  
        THIS RELAY, SIR.        


62
00:04:27,667 --> 00:04:29,367
    - WHAT'S THE PROBLEM, BAKER?
    - AAAH!                     


63
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:32,137
    WE'VE LOST THE DECOY SIGNAL.


64
00:04:32,206 --> 00:04:35,273
- GENTLEMEN, WE GOT             
  A TORPEDO ON OUR ASS.         
- TORPEDOES CLOSING, 300 YARDS. 


65
00:04:35,342 --> 00:04:37,608
        - THE DECOY SIGNAL'S    
          STILL DEAD, SIR.      
        - 200 YARDS.            


66
00:04:37,677 --> 00:04:40,545
    NINETY SECONDS              
    TO S.L.B.M. LAUNCH.         


67
00:04:40,613 --> 00:04:42,113
<i>COME ON, BAKER.</i>                 


68
00:04:42,182 --> 00:04:45,616
    - GOT IT.                   
      DECOY'S ON LINE, SIR.     
    -<i> [ Beeping ]</i>               


69
00:04:50,223 --> 00:04:52,557
            TORPEDO NUMBER ONE  
            JUST TOOK THE BAIT. 
            NUMBER TWO CLOSING. 


70
00:04:56,062 --> 00:04:58,396
                IT'S A MISS.    


71
00:04:58,465 --> 00:04:59,998
<i>ROSTOV'S</i> V.L.S. SYSTEM          
IS STILL READY.                 


72
00:05:00,066 --> 00:05:02,233
            THOSE NUKES FLY     
            IN ONE MINUTE, SIR. 


73
00:05:02,302 --> 00:05:04,469
    FORTY DEGREES STARBOARD.    
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>FORTY DEGREES STARBOARD.</i>        


74
00:05:04,538 --> 00:05:07,472
    STEADY ON COURSE...         
    ZERO NINE ZERO.             
<i>[ Man ] ZERO NINE ZERO.</i>         


75
00:05:07,541 --> 00:05:10,508
        SIR, SUGGEST WE FIRE    
        BOTH TORPEDOES NOW WHILE
        HE'S STILL IN RANGE.    


76
00:05:10,577 --> 00:05:12,143
                    <i> [ Jarod ]</i>  
                    <i> SIR.</i>       


77
00:05:13,446 --> 00:05:15,379
I RECOMMEND                     
THAT WE FIRE ONE NOW,           


78
00:05:15,448 --> 00:05:19,084
THAT WE VEER APPROXIMATELY      
30 DEGREES STARBOARD            
AND THEN FIRE TORPEDO TWO.      


79
00:05:19,152 --> 00:05:21,886
    - VEER? WHY DON'T WE JUST-- 
    - FIRE TORPEDO ONE.         


80
00:05:21,955 --> 00:05:24,088
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>FIRE ONE. AYE.</i>                  
<i>TORPEDO AWAY.</i>                   


81
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,159
        THIRTY SECONDS          
        UNTIL WARHEAD LAUNCH.   


82
00:05:28,228 --> 00:05:31,529
VEER THIRTY DEGREES STARBOARD.  
<i>[ Jarod ] RIGHT FULL RUDDER.</i>    


83
00:05:31,598 --> 00:05:34,198
        STEADY COURSE           
        ONE TWO ZERO.           


84
00:05:34,267 --> 00:05:37,002
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>RIGHT FULL RUDDER,</i>              
<i>ONE TWO ZERO. AYE.</i>              


85
00:05:37,071 --> 00:05:39,237
            ONE IS A MISS, SIR. 


86
00:05:41,641 --> 00:05:43,875
        - FIRE TWO.             
        - FIRE TWO. AYE.        


87
00:05:43,944 --> 00:05:46,778
    -<i> TORPEDO AWAY.</i>             
    - TWENTY SECONDS UNTIL      
      WARHEAD LAUNCH.           


88
00:05:51,118 --> 00:05:53,518
            THOSE BIRDS ARE HOT.


89
00:05:53,587 --> 00:05:55,553
            TEN SECONDS UNTIL   
            WARHEAD LAUNCH.     


90
00:06:01,528 --> 00:06:04,629
            NUMBER TWO IS       
            A DIRECT HIT.       
            SHE'S GOING DOWN.   


91
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:07,031
<i>[ Cheering, Clapping ]</i>          


92
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,367
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>THIS IS CAPTAIN DRUCKER</i>         
<i>OF THE</i> HARRISON.                


93
00:06:09,436 --> 00:06:12,570
<i>[ Mimics Russian Accent ]</i>       
<i>YOU'VE BLOWN US OUT OF WATER,</i>   
<i>YOU CRAZY YANKEE PIG.</i>           


94
00:06:12,639 --> 00:06:16,707
    ACKNOWLEDGED.               
    ALWAYS A PLEASURE TO RUN    
    A SIMULATION WITH YOU, TED. 


95
00:06:16,776 --> 00:06:19,110
<i>NEVER A COLD WAR</i>                
<i>WHEN YOU NEED ONE.</i>              
HARRISON<i> OUT.</i>                   


96
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:23,347
<i>YOU GOT NOTHING</i>                 
<i>TO SMILE ABOUT.</i>                 
<i>ANOTHER THREE SECONDS,</i>          


97
00:06:23,416 --> 00:06:25,883
    AND L.A.'s A PARKING LOT.   


98
00:06:28,154 --> 00:06:30,489
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>WAY TO GO, BAKER.</i>               


99
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,165
        <i> LIEUTENANT COMMANDER</i>   
        <i> FORRESTER,</i>             


100
00:06:40,233 --> 00:06:42,167
            <i> THIS CREW IS LOOSE.</i>


101
00:06:42,236 --> 00:06:44,202
IT'S TOO LOOSE.                 


102
00:06:44,271 --> 00:06:46,571
THE<i> MONROE</i> IS A TEAM,           
LIKE LINKS IN A CHAIN.          


103
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:48,940
    IF ONE OF THOSE LINKS       
    BREAKS UNDER STRESS,        


104
00:06:49,009 --> 00:06:52,243
    <i> WE SLIP THAT MUCH CLOSER</i>   
    <i> TO DISASTER.</i>               


105
00:06:53,980 --> 00:06:58,049
            [ Loudly ]          
            IN ONE WEEK,        
            WE HIT THE BIG BLUE.


106
00:06:58,117 --> 00:07:02,754
IT IS IMPERATIVE THAT           
YOUR RESPONSE TIMES IMPROVE.    


107
00:07:03,824 --> 00:07:06,290
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED             
ON OUR LAST TOUR,               


108
00:07:06,359 --> 00:07:09,694
    <i> I WANT THIS SHIP RUNNING</i>   
    <i> LIKE A DAMN SWISS WATCH.</i>   


109
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,166
        ALL RIGHT.              


110
00:07:15,235 --> 00:07:20,671
    YOU JUST TRADED YOUR DAY OFF
    FOR A RIDE ON MY PERSONAL   
    HIGHWAY TO HELL.            


111
00:07:24,711 --> 00:07:26,811
<i>[ Nashton ]</i>                     
<i>LEFT, LEFT, LEFT!</i>               


112
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:31,349
<i>COME ON, PEOPLE!</i>                
<i>IT'S A HIGHWAY TO HELL.</i>         
<i>WE LOVE IT!</i>                     


113
00:07:31,418 --> 00:07:33,351
<i>COME ON!</i>                        


114
00:07:33,420 --> 00:07:36,053
<i>HAVING FUN YET?</i>                 
        [ All ]                 
        YES, SIR!               


115
00:07:36,122 --> 00:07:38,690
<i>COME ON, PEOPLE!</i>                
<i>DO YOU LOVE IT?</i>                 


116
00:07:38,758 --> 00:07:41,293
            YES, SIR!           
<i>I CAN'T HEAR YOU!</i>               


117
00:07:41,361 --> 00:07:43,861
            YES, SIR!           


118
00:07:43,930 --> 00:07:47,198
<i>LET'S GO. LET'S GO.</i>             
<i>COME ON. LET'S GO. COME ON.</i>     


119
00:07:47,267 --> 00:07:49,667
<i>WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR?</i>       
<i>LET'S GO. MOVE IT.</i>              


120
00:07:49,736 --> 00:07:52,170
MOVE IT OUT. MOVE IT OUT.       
 MOVE IT OUT.                   
                [ Yells ]       


121
00:07:52,239 --> 00:07:55,673
        MOVE IT OUT!            
         MOVE! MOVE! MOVE!      


122
00:07:56,743 --> 00:07:58,776
    [ Jarod ]                   
    MOVE! MOVE! MOVE!           


123
00:07:58,845 --> 00:08:01,579
<i>[ All Shouting ]</i>                


124
00:08:05,085 --> 00:08:07,819
    I DIDN'T REALLY WANT        
    A DAY OFF. DID YOU, BAKER?  


125
00:08:07,887 --> 00:08:10,922
                        WHAT?   
YOU CAN'T EVEN HANDLE           
A LITTLE CIRCUIT FLARE-UP?      


126
00:08:10,991 --> 00:08:12,924
I MEAN, IF SOMETHING            
GOES WRONG THIS TOUR,           


127
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:16,027
YOU'RE NOT GONNA SCREW UP       
ON US LIKE YOU DID IN           
THE PUMP ROOM WITH SEAVER?      


128
00:08:16,096 --> 00:08:18,029
<i>SEAVER WAS A DUMB-ASS.</i>          


129
00:08:18,097 --> 00:08:21,032
                <i> [ Woman ]</i>      
                <i> HEY, GET HIM!</i>  
                <i> GET HIM!</i>       


130
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,868
[ All Yelling ]                 


131
00:08:23,937 --> 00:08:26,571
            [ Jarod ]           
            BREAK IT UP! GET UP!
            BREAK IT UP!        


132
00:08:26,639 --> 00:08:28,873
    KNOX! MARCUS!               


133
00:08:28,942 --> 00:08:30,975
        BAKER, YOU'VE GOT       
        THE HIGHEST RANK HERE.  


134
00:08:31,044 --> 00:08:33,411
        IF I EVEN CATCH YOU     
        LOOKING AT THESE SAILORS
        THE WRONG WAY,          


135
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:35,847
        I'M GONNA HAVE YOU      
        IN THE SCULLERY         
        EVERY DAY FOR A WEEK!   


136
00:08:35,916 --> 00:08:38,549
            UNDERSTOOD, SAILOR? 
YES, SIR!                       


137
00:08:41,521 --> 00:08:43,455
    FALL OUT!                   
<i>[ Man ] ALL RIGHT. MOVE OUT.</i>    


138
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:45,523
                    <i> [ Man #2 ]</i> 
                    <i> SIR.</i>       


139
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:56,334
    WELL, YOU HANDLED           
    THAT LITTLE SITUATION WELL. 


140
00:08:56,403 --> 00:08:59,937
        JUST AS WELL AS         
        MANEUVERS THIS MORNING. 


141
00:09:00,006 --> 00:09:02,106
SIR, I'M SORRY ABOUT THAT.      


142
00:09:02,175 --> 00:09:05,410
I DIDN'T MEAN TO                
STEP OUT OF LINE.               
            OH, YES, YOU DID.   


143
00:09:05,478 --> 00:09:07,878
        YOU'RE JUST LUCKY THAT  
        YOU MADE THE RIGHT CALL.


144
00:09:07,948 --> 00:09:11,882
I GUESS.                        
NAGEL SEEMED PRETTY STEAMED     
ABOUT THE LAST TOUR.            


145
00:09:11,952 --> 00:09:14,419
    YEAH, WELL, THAT'S          
    THE ONLY CHINK IN HIS ARMOR.


146
00:09:14,487 --> 00:09:18,056
            WE LOST A SAILOR.   
            THERE WAS A GAS LEAK
            IN THE PUMP ROOM.   


147
00:09:18,124 --> 00:09:20,825
A GAS LEAK?                     
                    YEAH. JX-5. 


148
00:09:20,893 --> 00:09:24,162
WHOA. A ROOMFUL OF THAT         
COULD'VE SET OFF                
THE ENTIRE SHIP.                


149
00:09:24,231 --> 00:09:26,164
        WHOO. TELL ME ABOUT IT. 


150
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,199
    I HAD THE DECK THAT NIGHT.  


151
00:09:28,268 --> 00:09:31,736
    IT'S PRETTY INTENSE.        
    IT'S NOT SOMETHING I WANT TO
    LIVE THROUGH AGAIN.         


152
00:09:32,739 --> 00:09:34,672
        HEY, TELL ME SOMETHING, 
        WILL YA?                


153
00:09:34,741 --> 00:09:37,341
        HOW DID YOU KNOW        
        THAT THE<i> HARRISON</i>       
        WAS GONNA CUT AND RUN?  


154
00:09:37,410 --> 00:09:40,344
"BULLDOG" TED DRUCKER           
WAS AT THE CONN.                


155
00:09:40,414 --> 00:09:43,581
IT'S HIS FAVORITE               
EVASIVE TECHNIQUE.              
        OH, YOU SERVED WITH HIM?


156
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:47,184
<i>ACTUALLY, JAROD'S</i>               
<i>FROM THE</i> GRANT,<i> SIR.</i>            
<i>LIEUTENANT PAULA PRATT.</i>         


157
00:09:47,253 --> 00:09:49,186
    AT EASE.                    


158
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:51,188
    SECURITY OFFICER.           


159
00:09:51,258 --> 00:09:53,190
    LIEUTENANT COMMANDER        
    JAROD FORRESTER.            


160
00:09:53,259 --> 00:09:56,661
YES. I JUST RAN THE REQUIRED    
CHECKS ON YOUR FILE.            


161
00:09:56,730 --> 00:09:59,798
YOUR DATES ON THE<i> GRANT</i>         
DON'T JIBE WITH                 
THE BUREAU OF PERSONNEL.        


162
00:10:01,601 --> 00:10:04,969
    SO WHY DON'T YOU            
    CALL THE<i> GRANT</i>              
    AND HAVE 'EM CLEAR IT UP?   


163
00:10:05,037 --> 00:10:09,473
I WILL. AS SOON AS              
SHE GETS BACK FROM              
A SILENT ESCORT IN ANTARCTICA.  


164
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:11,976
NEXT MONTH.                     


165
00:10:12,045 --> 00:10:14,345
COME SEE ME                     
AT P.S.D. TOMORROW.             


166
00:10:16,182 --> 00:10:18,116
    THAT WOMAN NEEDS A HOBBY.   


167
00:10:18,184 --> 00:10:20,451
SHE REMINDS ME OF SOMEONE       
I USED TO KNOW.                 


168
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:23,521
        GO THROUGH THE BOX      
        FROM JAROD'S LAST LAIR. 


169
00:10:23,589 --> 00:10:25,556
    CALL ME WITH SOLID LEADS.   


170
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,625
    [ Sydney ]                  
    WHERE WILL YOU BE,          
    MISS PARKER?                


171
00:10:27,693 --> 00:10:30,294
                OUT.            
            [ Beeps Off ]       


172
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:38,569
<i>WELL, THERE MUST BE SOMETHING</i>   
<i>YOU CAN TELL ME ABOUT MY MOTHER.</i>


173
00:10:38,638 --> 00:10:42,873
    IT'S BEEN NEARLY 30 YEARS,  
    BUT I REMEMBER HOW MUCH     
    SHE LOVED THE CHILDREN HERE.


174
00:10:42,942 --> 00:10:47,045
        I HAVE REASON TO BELIEVE
        THAT SHE MIGHT HAVE     
        RESCUED SOME OF THEM.   


175
00:10:47,113 --> 00:10:50,181
        RESCUED?                
            IT'S A LONG STORY.  


176
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:53,952
            DID SHE--           
            DID SHE BRING       
            ANY CHILDREN HERE?  


177
00:10:55,255 --> 00:10:57,655
NO. WE'VE ALWAYS GOTTEN         
OUR CHILDREN THE USUAL WAY:     


178
00:10:57,723 --> 00:11:01,525
ORPHANS, RUNAWAYS,              
VICTIMS OF CHILD ABUSE.         


179
00:11:01,594 --> 00:11:04,195
I'M AFRAID I WOULDN'T KNOW      
WHERE TO BEGIN.                 
                    [ Sighs ]   


180
00:11:06,199 --> 00:11:08,199
                    I MIGHT.    


181
00:11:14,007 --> 00:11:16,740
    I'M SORRY.                  
    NONE OF THEM RING A BELL.   


182
00:11:18,778 --> 00:11:20,778
THAT'S OKAY.                    


183
00:11:20,847 --> 00:11:23,448
YOU'VE BEEN--                   
 YOU'VE BEEN VERY HELPFUL.      


184
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:27,452
            WHO IS THIS JAROD   
            YOU'RE ASKING ABOUT?


185
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,787
AN ASSOCIATE.                   


186
00:11:29,856 --> 00:11:31,889
I THOUGHT MAYBE                 
HE MIGHT HAVE VISITED YOU.      


187
00:11:31,958 --> 00:11:34,391
                    NO.         


188
00:11:34,461 --> 00:11:39,129
<i>[ Sighs ]</i>                       
            IT'S NOT A DEAD END,
            MISS PARKER.        


189
00:11:43,235 --> 00:11:47,772
WELL, THE PERSON                
WHO GAVE THIS TO ME             
IS THE MASTER OF THE DEAD END.  


190
00:11:49,041 --> 00:11:51,008
        <i> YOU COULD MATCH THESE</i>  
        <i> WITH OUR FILES,</i>        


191
00:11:51,077 --> 00:11:53,444
    <i> BUT YOU'D HAVE TO GO DOWN</i>  
    <i> TO THE HALL OF RECORDS.</i>    


192
00:11:53,513 --> 00:11:55,680
            <i> ALL OF THESE KIDS</i>  
            <i> ARE PRE-1970.</i>      


193
00:11:55,748 --> 00:11:58,850
    <i> OUR FILES WERE DESTROYED</i>   
    <i> IN A FIRE THAT YEAR.</i>       


194
00:11:58,918 --> 00:12:01,051
    YOU HAD A FIRE IN 1970?     


195
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,788
                        <i> YES.</i>   


196
00:12:03,857 --> 00:12:05,790
            APRIL.              


197
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:08,793
            HOW DID YOU KNOW?   


198
00:12:11,230 --> 00:12:13,698
THAT'S WHEN MY MOTHER DIED.     


199
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,769
                    AT EASE.    


200
00:12:17,837 --> 00:12:20,237
            GOOD AFTERNOON, SIR.
GOOD AFTERNOON.                 


201
00:12:20,306 --> 00:12:23,374
        JUST WANT TO WELCOME YOU
        TO THE<i> MONROE.</i>          
    AT EASE.                    


202
00:12:23,443 --> 00:12:25,877
                UH, BAZOOKA.    


203
00:12:25,945 --> 00:12:28,212
        FROM MY PERSONAL STASH. 


204
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:30,548
    FOR ME?                     


205
00:12:30,617 --> 00:12:32,550
THIS IS INTERESTING.            


206
00:12:32,619 --> 00:12:35,319
BUBBLE GUM                      
NAMED AFTER A WEAPON.           


207
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:38,523
    HMM.                        


208
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,692
                WELL, IT'S BEEN 
                AROUND A WHILE. 


209
00:12:41,761 --> 00:12:43,761
IT'S VERY GOOD.                 


210
00:12:45,064 --> 00:12:47,432
AND IT COMES WITH               
ITS OWN PERSONAL STORY.         


211
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,634
[ Laughing ]                    
VERY CLEVER.                    


212
00:12:49,702 --> 00:12:53,638
    WELL, THANK YOU VERY MUCH.  
    AS YOU WERE.                
    [ Laughing ]                


213
00:13:00,447 --> 00:13:03,380
            <i> [ Girl ]</i>           
            <i> GET AWAY FROM ME!</i>  
            <i> LEAVE ME ALONE!</i>    


214
00:13:03,450 --> 00:13:06,551
            <i> I SAID GET--</i>       
            <i> GET AWAY FROM ME!</i>  


215
00:13:06,619 --> 00:13:08,552
            STOP IT!            


216
00:13:16,729 --> 00:13:18,662
[ Panting ]                     


217
00:13:18,731 --> 00:13:20,731
[ Yelps ]                       
        ARE YOU GOING SOMEPLACE?


218
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:23,701
LOOK, THERE'S TWO MEN           
CHASING ME. I THINK             
THEY'RE SOME KIND OF PERVERTS.  


219
00:13:23,770 --> 00:13:25,703
YOU'VE REALLY GOTTA HELP ME.    


220
00:13:25,772 --> 00:13:27,705
                    THAT'S THEM!
COMMANDER.                      


221
00:13:27,774 --> 00:13:30,541
    IS THERE SOME KIND OF       
    PROBLEM, SERGEANT?          


222
00:13:30,610 --> 00:13:33,644
YES, SIR.                       
WE CAUGHT THIS BUG TRYING TO    
HOT-WIRE AN ENSIGN'S JEEP.      


223
00:13:33,713 --> 00:13:37,881
OH, THAT'S A GREAT BIG LIE.     
BESIDES, I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW     
THE JEEP BELONGED TO THE ENSIGN.


224
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:42,686
<i>IT'S THE THIRD TIME</i>             
<i>THIS WEEK WE'VE HAD A RUN-IN</i>    
<i>WITH THIS DESPERADO.</i>            


225
00:13:44,858 --> 00:13:47,992
I SEE.                          
I THINK I CAN HANDLE IT         
FROM HERE.                      


226
00:13:49,729 --> 00:13:53,264
MY NAME'S JAROD.                
                MELINA PRATT.   


227
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:56,100
PRATT? AS IN                    
SECURITY OFFICER PRATT?         


228
00:13:56,169 --> 00:13:58,102
            AS IN HER DAUGHTER. 


229
00:13:58,171 --> 00:14:01,038
        YOU'RE GONNA TELL HER   
        ABOUT THIS, AREN'T YOU? 
WHAT ABOUT YOUR FATHER?         


230
00:14:01,107 --> 00:14:03,774
            HE'S THE NAVIGATOR  
            ON THE<i> FARRAGUT.</i>    


231
00:14:05,011 --> 00:14:08,646
THAT'S ON THE INDIAN OCEAN,     
ON PATROL?                      
                        YEAH.   


232
00:14:08,715 --> 00:14:11,115
HE'S BEEN GONE FOR              
ABOUT FOUR MONTHS NOW.          


233
00:14:11,183 --> 00:14:13,217
                FOUR AND A HALF.


234
00:14:13,285 --> 00:14:15,285
MUST BE PRETTY TOUGH            
ON YOU...                       


235
00:14:15,354 --> 00:14:17,588
AND YOUR MOTHER,                
YOUR FATHER BEING GONE          
THAT LONG.                      


236
00:14:17,657 --> 00:14:20,691
        MY MOM JUST WORKS MORE. 
        TO ME, IT'S NO BIGGIE.  


237
00:14:20,759 --> 00:14:24,729
SO YOUR DAD IS GONE,            
AND YOUR MOM WORKS ALL DAY.     


238
00:14:24,797 --> 00:14:28,699
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,         
A TEENAGER LIVES FOR            
THAT KIND OF FREEDOM.           


239
00:14:28,768 --> 00:14:30,734
<i>IS THAT TRUE?</i>                   


240
00:14:30,803 --> 00:14:34,105
IF YOU'RE SO INTERESTED IN      
TEENAGERS, MAYBE YOU SHOULD     
BECOME A HIGH SCHOOL COUNSELOR. 


241
00:14:34,173 --> 00:14:36,774
I ALREADY TRIED THAT ONCE.      
I MEAN, THE HOURS WERE GREAT,   
BUT...                          


242
00:14:36,843 --> 00:14:38,776
THE FOOD WAS TERRIBLE.          


243
00:14:41,047 --> 00:14:44,048
        SO, ARE YOU GONNA       
        TELL MY MOM ABOUT       
        THIS JEEP THING OR NOT? 


244
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:48,452
<i>MELINA.</i>                         
                WHAT?           


245
00:14:48,521 --> 00:14:50,554
NEXT TIME YOU GO TO             
SO MUCH TROUBLE...              


246
00:14:50,623 --> 00:14:52,623
TO GET INTO TROUBLE,            


247
00:14:52,691 --> 00:14:54,658
HOT-WIRE AN ADMIRAL'S JEEP.     


248
00:15:03,803 --> 00:15:06,003
<i>[ Man On P.A. ]</i>                 
<i>COMMUNICATIONS WATCH OFFICER</i>    
<i>AND D.D.O.,</i>                     


249
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:08,005
<i>PLEASE REPORT</i>                   
<i>TO THE QUARTERDECK.</i>             


250
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:11,008
<i>COMM WATCH OFFICER AND D.D.O.,</i>  
<i>REPORT TO THE QUARTERDECK.</i>      


251
00:15:11,076 --> 00:15:14,478
THAT'S NICE WORK...             
FOR AN OXYACETYLENE WELD.       


252
00:15:14,547 --> 00:15:18,316
IT'S OLD-SCHOOL, I KNOW,        
BUT IT HOLDS TIGHTER THAN       
ANY OF THAT NEWFANGLED STUFF.   


253
00:15:18,384 --> 00:15:20,318
            SNIPES ARE ALWAYS   
            GETTING ON ME.      


254
00:15:20,386 --> 00:15:22,953
            TIG WELD THIS,      
            GAS TUNGSTEN THAT.  


255
00:15:23,022 --> 00:15:25,222
        GOT NO RESPECT FOR      
        THE OLD WAYS, YOU KNOW. 


256
00:15:25,291 --> 00:15:27,458
I GUESS NOT.                    
                    [ Chuckles ]


257
00:15:28,461 --> 00:15:30,461
            EXCUSE ME.          


258
00:15:37,937 --> 00:15:39,871
                    AS YOU WERE.


259
00:15:39,940 --> 00:15:43,474
PETTY OFFICER MIKE BAKER.       
I PULLED HIM OUT OF A FIGHT     
A COUPLE OF DAYS AGO.           


260
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:45,809
    -<i> I HAVE A GOOD MIND</i>        
     <i> TO GO UP THERE--</i>          
    - WHOA, WHOA.               


261
00:15:45,878 --> 00:15:48,112
        I KNOW THAT YOU'RE      
        EAGER TO CRACK SKULLS,  
        BUT, UH,                


262
00:15:48,181 --> 00:15:50,114
        DON'T START ON BAKER.   


263
00:15:50,183 --> 00:15:52,783
        <i> HE LOST HIS BEST FRIEND</i>
        <i> ON OUR LAST TOUR.</i>      


264
00:15:52,852 --> 00:15:54,853
    SCOTT SEAVER.               


265
00:15:54,921 --> 00:15:58,456
I TOLD YOU ABOUT IT, JAROD.     
THE, UH, JX-5 LEAK              
IN THE PUMP ROOM.               


266
00:15:58,525 --> 00:16:02,060
- OH, YES. RIGHT.               
- SEAVER BOTCHED THE RETROFIT.  


267
00:16:02,128 --> 00:16:06,297
WHICH GAVE THE BOARD OF INQUIRY 
AN EXCUSE TO TRY TO MOTHBALL    
THE SHIP AGAIN.                 


268
00:16:06,365 --> 00:16:08,299
    <i> DAMN LEECHES CAME IN HERE.</i> 


269
00:16:08,368 --> 00:16:11,436
<i>THEY WENT OVER</i>                  
<i>EVERY PIECE OF PAPERWORK,</i>       
<i>EVERY INSPECTION RECORD,</i>        


270
00:16:11,504 --> 00:16:13,771
TRIED TO HAUL HER               
OUT OF THE WATER.               


271
00:16:13,840 --> 00:16:16,574
FINALLY, IT TOOK                
SEVEN ADMIRALS TO DECIDE...     


272
00:16:16,643 --> 00:16:19,543
THE PROBLEM WAS SEAVER'S        
SHODDY WORK.                    


273
00:16:19,612 --> 00:16:21,613
        I SEE.                  


274
00:16:21,681 --> 00:16:23,848
WELL, I GUESS                   
I'LL EASE OFF BAKER THEN.       


275
00:16:23,917 --> 00:16:27,318
        HE DOES KNOW            
        THAT HE'S ON THIS SHIP  
        FOR THE NEXT SIX MONTHS.


276
00:16:28,454 --> 00:16:31,189
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>WHERE HIS BEST FRIEND DIED.</i>     


277
00:18:32,846 --> 00:18:36,581
<i>[ Seaver's Voice ]</i>              
<i>OH, MY GOD!</i>                     
<i>BAKER, HELP ME!</i>                 


278
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:40,118
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>SURPRISE INSPECTION,</i>            
<i>OR ARE YOU STEALING STOCK TIPS?</i> 


279
00:18:40,186 --> 00:18:41,952
                <i> I WAS JUST...</i>  


280
00:18:42,021 --> 00:18:44,455
            GETTING TO KNOW     
            THE TERRITORY.      


281
00:18:46,926 --> 00:18:48,859
    YOU PLAY THE STOCK MARKET.  


282
00:18:48,928 --> 00:18:52,663
HEY, YOU WANT TO PUT A KID      
THROUGH COLLEGE ON MY SALARY,   
YOU GOTTA TAKE SOME CHANCES.    


283
00:18:52,732 --> 00:18:54,665
ACTUALLY, MY SON PICKS OUT      
ALL MY STOCKS.                  


284
00:18:54,734 --> 00:18:57,602
HE WANTS TO SEE                 
HIS TUITION KEEP COMING,        
HE BETTER PICK 'EM RIGHT.       


285
00:18:57,670 --> 00:19:00,905
        IS HE A BUSINESS MAJOR? 
HE'S A TIGHT END.               


286
00:19:00,974 --> 00:19:04,274
GOT A GOOD BRAIN.               
AVERAGE HANDS. NO SCHOLARSHIP.  


287
00:19:04,343 --> 00:19:08,980
BUT I'LL BE DAMNED              
HE'S GONNA SPEND HIS WHOLE LIFE 
SWEATING IN A HOLE LIKE THIS.   


288
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:13,584
YOU SURE THIS AIN'T             
NO INSPECTION?                  
                    PROMISE.    


289
00:19:13,652 --> 00:19:15,653
GOOD. I MEAN,                   
NOTHING PERSONAL, SIR,          
BUT, UH,                        


290
00:19:15,721 --> 00:19:17,688
I'VE BEEN TURNING               
WRENCHES DOWN HERE...           


291
00:19:17,757 --> 00:19:20,257
SINCE YOU AND MOST OF THIS CREW 
WERE PLAYING KICK THE CAN.      


292
00:19:20,326 --> 00:19:23,361
    AND WHAT CAN WAS I KICKING? 


293
00:19:24,898 --> 00:19:28,365
ALL I'M SAYING IS, UH,          
YOU DON'T NEED TO GO            
WASTING YOUR TIME...            


294
00:19:28,435 --> 00:19:30,601
CHECKING UP ON                  
LIEUTENANT ALBERT DANES.        


295
00:19:30,670 --> 00:19:32,603
                    AS YOU WERE.


296
00:19:32,672 --> 00:19:35,573
THANK YOU, SIR.                 
 THANK YOU.                     


297
00:19:40,547 --> 00:19:43,347
<i>[ Man Shouting Commands</i>         
<i>  In Distance ]</i>                 


298
00:19:46,419 --> 00:19:48,352
    [ Laughing ]                


299
00:19:59,432 --> 00:20:01,365
THEY'RE VERY FUNNY.             


300
00:20:02,368 --> 00:20:04,302
        THEY STILL MAKE THOSE?  


301
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:08,372
<i>[ Jarod ] YEAH.</i>                 
<i>BUT WHAT I DON'T UNDERSTAND IS</i>  
<i>WHY DOES HE WEAR THE EYE PATCH?</i> 


302
00:20:10,276 --> 00:20:13,377
    MATTERS OF COSMIC IMPORTANCE
    I'M NOT PREPARED TO ADDRESS.


303
00:20:13,446 --> 00:20:15,379
    HUH.                        


304
00:20:15,448 --> 00:20:18,382
    I WANTED YOU HERE           
    WHEN I CALL ADMIRAL MASON.  


305
00:20:18,451 --> 00:20:20,384
YOU REMEMBER ADMIRAL MASON.     


306
00:20:20,453 --> 00:20:23,020
HE SIGNED YOUR RECOMMENDATION.  


307
00:20:23,089 --> 00:20:25,189
        HOW COULD I FORGET?     


308
00:20:25,258 --> 00:20:28,159
            <i> [ Autodial Beeps,</i>  
              <i> Line Ringing ]</i>   


309
00:20:28,228 --> 00:20:30,161
        <i> [ Woman ]</i>              
        <i> ADMIRAL MASON'S OFFICE.</i>


310
00:20:30,230 --> 00:20:33,397
LIEUTENANT PAULA PRATT          
CALLING FROM                    
LONG BEACH NAVAL STATION.       


311
00:20:33,466 --> 00:20:36,600
<i>[ Woman ] I'M SORRY.</i>            
<i>THE ADMIRAL IS ON HIS</i>           
<i>ANNUAL FISHING TRIP TO BIMINI.</i>  


312
00:20:36,669 --> 00:20:38,902
<i>[ Pratt ]</i>                       
<i>IT'S NICE SOMEBODY</i>              
<i>HAS TIME FOR A VACATION.</i>        


313
00:20:38,971 --> 00:20:41,572
HOW LONG WILL HE BE GONE?       
                    <i> [ Woman ]</i>  
                    <i> TWO WEEKS.</i> 


314
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:46,109
<i>AND HE LEFT STRICT ORDERS</i>       
<i>NOT TO BE DISTURBED--</i>           
<i>UNLESS, OF COURSE, IT'S URGENT.</i> 


315
00:20:48,948 --> 00:20:51,081
    I'LL CALL BACK.             


316
00:20:51,150 --> 00:20:52,449
        - BUMMER.               
        - BUMMER?               


317
00:20:52,518 --> 00:20:54,385
<i>MELINA,</i>                         
<i>SHE'S BUSY!</i>                     
    THAT'S WHAT JOE WOULD SAY.  


318
00:20:54,454 --> 00:20:56,654
<i>I DON'T CARE HOW BUSY SHE IS.</i>   
<i> I NEED TO SEE HER!</i>             


319
00:20:56,723 --> 00:20:58,689
<i>MELINA, I'M IN A MEETING.</i>       


320
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:00,390
                I KNOW.         


321
00:21:00,459 --> 00:21:01,792
                    HI.         


322
00:21:03,696 --> 00:21:07,231
BUT I CAN'T EVEN GET AN         
APPOINTMENT, AND I NEED TO KNOW 
TODAY IF I CAN GO SEE R.E.M.    


323
00:21:07,299 --> 00:21:09,300
            RAPID EYE MOVEMENTS?


324
00:21:09,368 --> 00:21:12,269
        - NO. IT'S A BAND.      
        - OH.                   


325
00:21:12,338 --> 00:21:14,105
- TICKETS GO ON SALE IN AN HOUR.
- I TOLD YOU.                   


326
00:21:14,174 --> 00:21:16,407
            <i> I DON'T WANT YOU</i>   
            <i> GOING ALONE.</i>       


327
00:21:16,476 --> 00:21:19,477
        I WON'T BE ALONE, MOM.  
        THERE'LL BE 40,000      
        OTHER PEOPLE THERE.     


328
00:21:19,546 --> 00:21:22,580
[ Sighs ]                       
I AM BUSY.                      
WE WILL TALK ABOUT THIS LATER.  


329
00:21:22,649 --> 00:21:24,649
        YEAH, WHAT ELSE IS NEW? 


330
00:21:29,956 --> 00:21:31,789
    MY DAUGHTER.                


331
00:22:34,387 --> 00:22:37,588
YO. WHAT'S UP?                  
    WHY WON'T YOU TALK TO ME?   


332
00:22:37,657 --> 00:22:39,657
                [ Chattering ]  


333
00:22:43,796 --> 00:22:45,562
    HOW'D YOUR TATTOO COME OUT? 


334
00:22:45,631 --> 00:22:47,465
WHAT ARE YOU, STALKING ME?      


335
00:22:47,533 --> 00:22:50,034
                NOT EXACTLY.    


336
00:22:50,102 --> 00:22:52,903
            THIS POLICE OFFICER 
            STOPPED BY AND, UH, 


337
00:22:52,972 --> 00:22:54,905
            LEFT YOU            
            THIS PARKING TICKET.


338
00:22:54,974 --> 00:22:57,141
            GREAT.              


339
00:22:57,210 --> 00:22:59,310
MY MOM'S GONNA GO BALLISTIC     
WHEN SHE SEES THIS.             


340
00:22:59,379 --> 00:23:02,146
            NOT TO MENTION      
            WHEN SHE FINDS OUT  
            YOU STOLE HER CAR.  


341
00:23:02,215 --> 00:23:06,717
BUT HAVING HER GO BALLISTIC--   
THAT'S THE GENERAL IDEA,        
ISN'T IT?                       


342
00:23:22,068 --> 00:23:24,502
COME ON. YOU CAN DO IT.         
TRY IT AGAIN.                   


343
00:23:24,571 --> 00:23:28,205
WRAP IT AROUND                  
YOUR TONGUE AND...              


344
00:23:28,274 --> 00:23:30,274
    BLOW.                       


345
00:23:31,978 --> 00:23:33,944
[ Laughs ]                      
                        YES!    


346
00:23:34,013 --> 00:23:37,948
I CAN'T BELIEVE NO ONE TAUGHT   
YOU HOW TO BLOW BUBBLE GUM.     
    I HAD A LONELY CHILDHOOD.   


347
00:23:38,017 --> 00:23:40,183
YEAH, JOIN THE CLUB.            


348
00:23:42,789 --> 00:23:46,023
        <i> "I.L.Y."</i>               
        <i> IS THAT ANOTHER BAND?</i>  


349
00:23:46,092 --> 00:23:50,962
NO. JUST THREE LETTERS          
I WANT TO REMEMBER.             
THAT'S ALL.                     


350
00:23:52,164 --> 00:23:54,098
        WHAT ARE YOUR PARENTS   
        GOING TO SAY?           


351
00:23:54,167 --> 00:23:56,099
I DON'T CARE.                   


352
00:23:56,169 --> 00:23:59,803
MY MOM HATES ME,                
AND MY DAD'S NEVER AROUND.      
    YOUR MOM DOES NOT HATE YOU. 


353
00:23:59,872 --> 00:24:03,474
    PARENTS LOVE THEIR CHILDREN.
OH, WHAT SITCOM                 
ARE YOU LIVING IN?              


354
00:24:11,383 --> 00:24:13,317
                [ Laughs ]      


355
00:24:49,489 --> 00:24:52,289
<i>[ Bubble Pops ]</i>                 
<i>[ Man On Recording ]</i>            
<i>IN CONCLUSION,</i>                  


356
00:24:52,358 --> 00:24:56,594
VICTIM SEAVER EXPIRED AFTER     
INHALING THE JX-5 TOXIC GAS     
FROM THE SHIP'S COOLANT SYSTEM. 


357
00:24:56,662 --> 00:25:01,198
<i>ICE CRYSTALS FORMED</i>             
<i>IN THE LUNGS WITHIN 30 SECONDS,</i> 
<i>RESULTING IN ASPHYXIATION.</i>      


358
00:25:01,267 --> 00:25:03,433
FURTHERMORE,                    
ADDITIONAL TRAUMA--             


359
00:25:21,688 --> 00:25:25,122
<i>[ Seaver ]</i>                      
<i>BAKER! BAKER!</i>                   
<i>OH, MY GOD!</i>                     


360
00:25:25,191 --> 00:25:27,758
<i>CAN'T SLEEP?</i>                    
                    SIR.        


361
00:25:28,895 --> 00:25:32,396
AT EASE, SAILOR.                
SIT DOWN.                       


362
00:25:42,641 --> 00:25:44,641
I HAVE NIGHTMARES TOO.          


363
00:25:46,112 --> 00:25:48,212
ABOUT FAMILY                    
I'VE NEVER SEEN,                


364
00:25:49,548 --> 00:25:51,615
BEST FRIENDS I'VE LOST.         


365
00:25:57,623 --> 00:26:00,924
    SCOTT SEAVER DID NOT        
    BOTCH THAT RETROFIT, SIR.   


366
00:26:00,993 --> 00:26:04,395
        AND JUST BECAUSE        
        SOME BIG PANEL          
        OF ADMIRALS SAYS SO--   


367
00:26:04,464 --> 00:26:06,163
DOESN'T MEAN IT'S TRUE.         


368
00:26:08,667 --> 00:26:10,667
                    RIGHT.      


369
00:26:13,773 --> 00:26:15,706
            SCOTT WAS EDGY...   


370
00:26:15,775 --> 00:26:17,707
            THE WHOLE WEEK      
            BEFORE IT HAPPENED. 


371
00:26:19,245 --> 00:26:21,779
        I THINK HE KNEW         
        THERE WAS SOMETHING     
        WRONG WITH THE<i> MONROE,</i>  


372
00:26:21,847 --> 00:26:24,615
        BUT HE NEVER WOULD'VE   
        LET US DEPLOY LIKE THAT.


373
00:26:28,921 --> 00:26:30,854
                LOOK,           


374
00:26:30,923 --> 00:26:35,059
YOU DON'T GOTTA WORRY ABOUT ME  
GETTING TANKED OR GETTING INTO  
FIGHTS ANYMORE, SIR.            


375
00:26:35,127 --> 00:26:37,528
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?     


376
00:26:37,597 --> 00:26:39,930
            I'M GONNA TALK TO   
            LIEUTENANT PRATT.   


377
00:26:39,999 --> 00:26:41,932
            I'M OUT OF HERE.    


378
00:26:42,001 --> 00:26:44,702
YOU'RE GOING TO RESIGN.         


379
00:26:44,770 --> 00:26:46,704
<i>YOU THINK THAT'S GOING TO</i>       
<i>SOLVE ANYTHING?</i>                 


380
00:26:46,772 --> 00:26:49,139
        I WATCHED HIM DIE, SIR. 


381
00:26:53,780 --> 00:26:57,514
    YOU KNOW, UH,               
    IT HIT US OUT OF NOWHERE.   


382
00:26:57,583 --> 00:27:03,320
    THE PIPE BURST,             
    AND THE WHOLE PLACE         
    WAS FILLING UP WITH JX-5.   


383
00:27:03,389 --> 00:27:06,356
        SCOTT TOLD ME TO        
        GET OUT OF THERE.       


384
00:27:06,425 --> 00:27:09,193
    HE SAID HE COULD HANDLE IT. 


385
00:27:11,197 --> 00:27:13,197
        I COULD'VE SAVED HIM.   


386
00:27:16,135 --> 00:27:18,335
        BUT THEN NASHTON        
        SEALED THE HATCH.       


387
00:27:18,404 --> 00:27:20,470
            NASHTON.            


388
00:27:20,539 --> 00:27:22,639
        <i> I COULD SEE SCOTT...</i>   


389
00:27:22,708 --> 00:27:24,641
        THROUGH THE PORTAL.     


390
00:27:24,710 --> 00:27:27,144
<i>THE GAS WAS</i>                     
<i>STARTING TO GET TO HIM.</i>         


391
00:27:28,848 --> 00:27:31,114
        WELL, FIRST IT          
        MAKES YOU CRAZY.        


392
00:27:32,150 --> 00:27:35,252
        FILLS UP YOUR LUNGS     
        AND FREEZES 'EM.        


393
00:27:36,889 --> 00:27:38,822
        <i> HE COULDN'T BREATHE.</i>   


394
00:27:51,403 --> 00:27:53,336
            WAIT.               


395
00:27:53,405 --> 00:27:56,140
        THE X.O. WAS ON DECK    
        THAT NIGHT.             


396
00:27:56,208 --> 00:27:58,942
    NOW, WHY WOULD NASHTON      
    COME DOWN HERE              
    TO SEAL THE HATCH?          


397
00:28:00,245 --> 00:28:03,047
        HE SAID THE WHOLE SHIP  
        COULD'VE BLOWN.         


398
00:28:03,115 --> 00:28:05,683
        HE SAID HE HAD TO       
        SEAL THE HATCH.         


399
00:28:12,058 --> 00:28:15,292
    SOME BEST FRIEND            
    I TURNED OUT TO BE, HUH?    


400
00:28:19,364 --> 00:28:21,932
    HE DIDN'T HAVE TO DIE, SIR. 


401
00:28:23,969 --> 00:28:26,503
        I SHOULD'VE STAYED.     


402
00:28:29,108 --> 00:28:32,142
        IT SHOULD'VE BEEN ME    
        THAT DIED.              


403
00:28:33,212 --> 00:28:35,613
    IT WASN'T YOUR FAULT.       


404
00:28:45,490 --> 00:28:48,558
<i>[ Nashton ]</i>                     
<i>THERE'S BEEN A LOT OF TALK</i>      
<i>ABOUT DECOMMISSIONING HER,</i>      


405
00:28:48,627 --> 00:28:51,261
<i>BUT I'M HERE</i>                    
<i>TO TELL YOU GENTLEMEN</i>           
<i>THAT THE U.S.S.</i> MONROE...       


406
00:28:51,330 --> 00:28:53,263
<i>IS A LONG WAY FROM MOTHBALLS.</i>   


407
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:58,535
THIS ACCIDENT--                 
 THIS TRAGEDY--                 


408
00:28:58,603 --> 00:29:03,740
HAPPENED BECAUSE OF SUBSTANDARD 
WORK BY A YOUNG ENGINEER        
NAMED SCOTT SEAVER.             


409
00:29:03,809 --> 00:29:08,578
<i>[ Man ] YOU BELIEVE THAT</i>        
<i>SEALING THAT ROOM WAS</i>           
<i>THE CORRECT COURSE OF ACTION.</i>   


410
00:29:08,647 --> 00:29:11,882
JX-5 GAS MIGHT HAVE SEEPED      
TO THE REST OF THE SHIP.        


411
00:29:11,951 --> 00:29:14,884
    SHE WAS A POWDER KEG,       
    READY TO BLOW.              


412
00:29:14,953 --> 00:29:18,455
IF I HAD HAD THE TIME TO PULL   
HIM OUT, I WOULD HAVE DONE SO.  


413
00:29:18,523 --> 00:29:23,794
<i>AS RANKING OFFICERS,</i>            
<i>THESE ARE THE KINDS OF CALLS</i>    
<i>THAT WE'RE EXPECTED TO MAKE.</i>    


414
00:29:23,863 --> 00:29:26,930
    IT'S ONE OF THE DEMONS      
    WE HAVE TO LIVE WITH.       


415
00:29:28,367 --> 00:29:31,034
I DID IT TO SAVE THE SHIP.      


416
00:29:31,103 --> 00:29:34,304
YOU DID IT... TO SAVE YOUR JOB. 


417
00:29:36,509 --> 00:29:38,509
                <i> [ Door Opens ]</i> 


418
00:29:38,577 --> 00:29:40,577
    <i> [ Footsteps Approaching ]</i>  


419
00:29:40,646 --> 00:29:42,646
                <i> [ Door Closes ]</i>


420
00:29:51,690 --> 00:29:53,690
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>THE DOOR WAS OPEN.</i>              


421
00:30:01,367 --> 00:30:04,935
<i>MAKING HOUSE CALLS NOW, SYD?</i>    
    WHERE WERE YOU TODAY?       


422
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:11,408
LAST TIME I CHECKED,            
THAT WAS A RAINES QUESTION.     


423
00:30:15,213 --> 00:30:17,814
<i>WHAT KIND OF GAME</i>               
<i>ARE YOU PLAYING WITH JAROD?</i>     


424
00:30:19,718 --> 00:30:21,651
                GAME?           


425
00:30:21,720 --> 00:30:23,320
HALL OF RECORDS.                


426
00:30:25,223 --> 00:30:27,857
<i>YOU'RE STARTING TO</i>              
<i>ASK QUESTIONS.</i>                  


427
00:30:27,926 --> 00:30:29,859
THE WAY YOUR MOTHER DID.        


428
00:30:31,230 --> 00:30:33,830
<i>HER FINAL SESSION WITH ME,</i>      


429
00:30:33,898 --> 00:30:36,065
BEFORE SHE GOT ON THE ELEVATOR, 


430
00:30:37,536 --> 00:30:39,469
SHE WAS LOOKING FOR ANSWERS.    


431
00:30:39,538 --> 00:30:42,239
    SHE DIDN'T HAVE THE MEANS   
    TO FIND THEM.               


432
00:30:42,307 --> 00:30:46,142
- I DO.                         
- THEN YOU'LL END UP LIKE HER.  


433
00:30:49,948 --> 00:30:51,881
            IS THAT A THREAT?   


434
00:30:51,950 --> 00:30:53,883
    A WARNING...                


435
00:30:54,886 --> 00:30:56,919
    FROM A FRIEND.              


436
00:31:17,175 --> 00:31:19,109
            MAIL CALL.          


437
00:31:19,178 --> 00:31:22,111
    THESE SEEM TO HAVE SLIPPED  
    THROUGH THE CRACKS.         


438
00:31:22,181 --> 00:31:25,516
HEY. PERSONAL DELIVERY          
FROM THE OPS OFFICER.           


439
00:31:25,584 --> 00:31:28,085
<i>THANKS.</i>                         


440
00:31:28,153 --> 00:31:31,688
LETTER FROM MY KID AT COLLEGE.  
GONNA BE AN ENGINEER.           


441
00:31:31,756 --> 00:31:33,690
                OH, YEAH?       


442
00:31:33,759 --> 00:31:35,725
            CORNELL.            
            MUST BE EXPENSIVE.  


443
00:31:35,794 --> 00:31:38,995
    - HOW'D YOU KNOW            
      HE WAS GOING THERE?       
    - INTERESTING.              


444
00:31:40,098 --> 00:31:43,032
        THIS IS                 
        AN OXYACETYLENE WELD.   


445
00:31:43,101 --> 00:31:45,034
        NOW, SCOTT SEAVER,      


446
00:31:45,104 --> 00:31:47,104
        HE WAS ONLY RATED FOR   
        GAS TUNGSTEN WELDING.   


447
00:31:47,172 --> 00:31:50,106
    <i> IF THOSE ADMIRALS HAD KNOWN</i>
    <i> WHAT TO LOOK FOR,</i>          


448
00:31:50,175 --> 00:31:53,109
            THEY WOULD'VE KNOWN 
            THAT SEAVER DIDN'T  
            BOTCH THE RETROFIT. 


449
00:31:55,847 --> 00:31:58,949
        NASHTON FORCED YOU      
        TO DO THE WORK,         


450
00:31:59,018 --> 00:32:03,152
        <i> AFTER IT RUPTURED,</i>     
        <i> AND MAKE IT LOOK LIKE</i>  
        <i> SEAVER BOTCHED IT.</i>     


451
00:32:03,221 --> 00:32:06,423
    - COME ON. THAT'S CRAZY.    
    - TELL THAT TO SCOTT SEAVER.


452
00:32:06,491 --> 00:32:08,925
    <i> I SPOKE TO HIS BEST FRIEND.</i>


453
00:32:08,994 --> 00:32:12,362
    HE SAID SEAVER WAS NERVOUS  
    THE WHOLE WEEK              
    BEFORE THE DEPLOY.          


454
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:15,698
        HE KNEW SOMETHING       
        WAS WRONG, DIDN'T HE?   


455
00:32:15,767 --> 00:32:18,435
WITH ALL DUE RESPECT, SIR.      
YOU'VE LOST IT.                 


456
00:32:18,503 --> 00:32:22,305
DID NASHTON THREATEN            
YOUR CAREER, OR DID HE THREATEN 
YOUR SON'S EDUCATION?           


457
00:32:24,509 --> 00:32:26,877
WHAT'S THE DIFFERENCE?          


458
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:29,679
NASHTON SAID HE WAS GONNA TURN  
THE INVESTIGATING PANEL ON ME.  


459
00:32:29,748 --> 00:32:32,014
    I'D HAVE BEEN               
    KICKED OUT ON MY ASS.       


460
00:32:32,083 --> 00:32:34,017
    NO PENSION, NO NOTHING.     


461
00:32:34,086 --> 00:32:37,020
<i>AND HE FORCED SEAVER AND ME</i>     
<i>TO SIGN OFF ON THAT</i>             
<i>INSPECTION REPORT...</i>            


462
00:32:37,089 --> 00:32:39,823
    EVEN THOUGH THE JX-5 LINE   
    NEEDED WORK.                


463
00:32:39,892 --> 00:32:41,825
    BRASS NEVER KNEW.           


464
00:32:41,894 --> 00:32:45,428
        AND THE EXTRA WORK      
        WOULD HAVE DELAYED      
        DEPLOYMENT.             


465
00:32:45,497 --> 00:32:49,266
    OR WORSE,                   
    PUT THE<i> MONROE</i> IN MOTHBALLS.


466
00:32:50,535 --> 00:32:52,668
        NO MORE<i> MONROE,</i>         


467
00:32:52,737 --> 00:32:54,837
    NO MORE CAREER FOR NASHTON. 


468
00:32:57,642 --> 00:32:59,642
        SO A 20-YEAR-OLD KID... 


469
00:32:59,711 --> 00:33:01,711
            CHOKES TO DEATH.    


470
00:33:02,915 --> 00:33:06,049
- IT COULD'VE BEEN YOUR SHIFT.  
- OH, COME ON.                  


471
00:33:06,117 --> 00:33:09,786
NASHTON TRIED TO SAVE           
THAT POOR KID. THE PUMP ROOM WAS
GONNA BLOW. THERE WAS NO TIME.  


472
00:33:09,855 --> 00:33:12,622
    <i> THERE WAS PLENTY OF TIME.</i>  
    <i> BUT SEAVER KNEW THE TRUTH.</i> 


473
00:33:14,125 --> 00:33:16,125
        NASHTON MADE SURE       
        HE DIED WITH IT.        


474
00:33:20,932 --> 00:33:23,967
<i>[ Car Alarm</i>                     
<i>  Blaring In Distance ]</i>         


475
00:33:24,036 --> 00:33:26,736
<i>[ Bottle Rattles ]</i>              


476
00:33:26,805 --> 00:33:29,639
<i>[ Car Alarm Continues Blaring ]</i> 


477
00:33:32,544 --> 00:33:34,577
<i>[ Car Alarm Stops ]</i>             


478
00:33:35,814 --> 00:33:38,081
YOUR MOM'S GOING TO MISS YOU.   


479
00:33:51,196 --> 00:33:54,263
        YEAH, WELL, YOU CAN'T   
        MISS SOMETHING THAT'S   
        NOT THERE TO BEGIN WITH.


480
00:33:54,332 --> 00:33:56,833
            I'M NOT GOING       
            BACK THERE-- EVER.  


481
00:33:57,836 --> 00:33:59,836
OKAY.                           


482
00:34:04,109 --> 00:34:07,510
YOU FEEL LIKE                   
YOU'RE NOT VERY IMPORTANT,      
DON'T YOU?                      


483
00:34:09,714 --> 00:34:13,416
YOU FEEL LIKE...                
 YOU WERE FORGOTTEN,            


484
00:34:13,485 --> 00:34:17,520
BUT YOU HAVEN'T BEEN.           
            YEAH, WHAT DO YOU   
            KNOW ABOUT IT?      


485
00:34:17,589 --> 00:34:20,223
I DON'T EVEN KNOW               
WHO MY PARENTS ARE.             


486
00:34:22,860 --> 00:34:24,894
I DON'T KNOW                    
IF THEY GAVE ME UP...           


487
00:34:24,963 --> 00:34:27,229
OR I WAS TAKEN FROM THEM.       


488
00:34:29,668 --> 00:34:33,536
BUT I KNOW...                   
THEY'RE STILL OUT THERE.        


489
00:34:34,606 --> 00:34:36,606
SOMEWHERE.                      


490
00:34:38,677 --> 00:34:40,777
I KNOW THEY LOVE ME.            


491
00:34:40,846 --> 00:34:43,847
DEEP DOWN INSIDE,               
I KNOW THEY LOVE ME.            
                    [ Sobs ]    


492
00:34:43,915 --> 00:34:47,217
JUST LIKE DEEP DOWN INSIDE      
YOU KNOW YOUR PARENTS LOVE YOU. 


493
00:34:50,856 --> 00:34:54,457
    MY MOM JUST BURIES HERSELF  
    IN WORK EVERY TIME          
    MY DAD'S OUT TO SEA.        


494
00:34:56,161 --> 00:34:59,395
YOUR MOM IS RESPONSIBLE         
FOR A LOT OF PEOPLE'S LIVES.    


495
00:34:59,464 --> 00:35:04,334
MAYBE IN ALL THAT, SHE OVERLOOKS
THE LIFE THAT'S MOST IMPORTANT  
TO HER, BUT I KNOW...           


496
00:35:04,402 --> 00:35:06,836
SHE LOVES YOU VERY MUCH.        


497
00:35:12,211 --> 00:35:14,377
        I REALLY MISS MY DAD.   


498
00:35:22,588 --> 00:35:25,121
        "I LOVE YOU."           


499
00:35:26,491 --> 00:35:29,159
                I.L.Y.          


500
00:35:29,227 --> 00:35:33,362
    MY DAD USED TO PUT IT ON ALL
    THE SATELLITE COMMUNICATIONS
    HE'D SEND US FROM THE SUBS. 


501
00:35:33,431 --> 00:35:38,769
YOU KNOW, THEY ONLY GIVE YOU,   
LIKE, 40 WORDS TO SAY EVERYTHING
YOU CAN TO EACH OTHER,          


502
00:35:38,837 --> 00:35:41,304
        SO YOU GOTTA ABBREVIATE.


503
00:35:46,944 --> 00:35:50,112
        I JUST WISH HE WAS HERE 
        TO SAY IT IN PERSON.    


504
00:35:52,083 --> 00:35:54,718
    SHH, SHH, SHH.              


505
00:35:56,688 --> 00:35:58,688
    SHH.                        


506
00:36:19,978 --> 00:36:22,112
                SORRY, MAMA.    


507
00:36:23,115 --> 00:36:25,115
I'M SORRY TOO, HONEY.           


508
00:36:27,119 --> 00:36:29,085
WE'LL TALK INSIDE.              
                I'M SORRY.      


509
00:36:29,154 --> 00:36:31,154
IT'S OKAY.                      


510
00:36:32,557 --> 00:36:35,959
    - YOU HAVE A GREAT KID.     
    - YEAH.                     


511
00:36:37,930 --> 00:36:40,730
I THINK I SHOULD TELL HER THAT  
A LITTLE MORE OFTEN.            


512
00:36:42,468 --> 00:36:44,400
            THANKS.             


513
00:36:44,469 --> 00:36:47,003
            [ Engine Starts ]   


514
00:37:20,405 --> 00:37:23,073
    ARE YOU SURE THAT RESIGNING 
    IS THE RIGHT THING TO DO?   


515
00:37:23,141 --> 00:37:25,141
MADE UP MY MIND, SIR.           


516
00:37:27,979 --> 00:37:30,780
- DID I SAY "AT EASE," SAILOR?  
- NO, SIR!                      


517
00:37:30,849 --> 00:37:33,249
        ARE YOU SURE            
        IT'S THE RIGHT THING    
        TO DO, SAILOR?          


518
00:37:33,318 --> 00:37:36,920
YES, SIR!                       
    IS THAT WHAT SCOTT SEAVER   
    WOULD HAVE WANTED?          


519
00:37:36,988 --> 00:37:39,155
                HOPE TO SEE YOU 
                ON BOARD,       


520
00:37:40,158 --> 00:37:42,092
                        SAILOR. 


521
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:44,160
                        AT EASE.


522
00:37:49,033 --> 00:37:52,135
[ Young Jarod ]                 
WHAT'S THAT, SYDNEY?            
[ Young Sydney ] I DON'T KNOW.  


523
00:37:52,204 --> 00:37:54,604
            [ Woman Screaming ] 
            NO! NO! NO.         


524
00:37:54,673 --> 00:37:56,606
    THEY'RE TRYING TO HURT HER. 


525
00:37:56,675 --> 00:37:58,408
[ Young Sydney ]                
STAY HERE, JAROD.               
                NO!             


526
00:37:58,477 --> 00:38:01,077
    - NO.                       
    - [ Man ]                   
      GET HER ON THE ELEVATOR!  


527
00:38:01,146 --> 00:38:03,113
                <i> [ Phone Rings ]</i>
[ Gunshot ]                     


528
00:38:03,181 --> 00:38:05,581
[ Man ]                         
GET THE KID OUT OF HERE!        
[ Young Jarod ] STOP!           


529
00:38:05,651 --> 00:38:09,418
- WHAT?                         
- JAROD HAS THEM, DOESN'T HE?   


530
00:38:09,487 --> 00:38:11,587
                    <i> HAS WHAT?</i>  


531
00:38:11,657 --> 00:38:13,656
THE ANSWERS                     
YOU'RE LOOKING FOR.             


532
00:38:13,724 --> 00:38:16,993
    WHEN I CATCH HIM,           
    I'LL JUST HAVE TO FIND OUT. 


533
00:38:17,062 --> 00:38:19,362
    YOU MAY HAVE THAT CHANCE.   


534
00:38:20,766 --> 00:38:24,066
COMMANDER JAROD FORRESTER       
IS CURRENTLY SERVING ABOARD...  


535
00:38:24,135 --> 00:38:26,536
THE DESTROYER U.S.S.<i> MONROE.</i>    


536
00:38:26,604 --> 00:38:29,906
    ONE OF BROOTS'S             
    ROUTINE SCANS CAUGHT IT.    


537
00:38:31,309 --> 00:38:35,745
        HOWEVER,                
        NAVAL INTELLIGENCE      
        MAY ALREADY BE ONTO HIM.


538
00:38:35,814 --> 00:38:39,249
        NAVAL INTELLIGENCE?     
    THAT'S CORRECT.             


539
00:38:39,318 --> 00:38:41,384
        HAVE MY FATHER          
        CALL THE SECRETARY.     


540
00:38:41,453 --> 00:38:43,453
YES, MISS PARKER.               
            MMM.                


541
00:38:43,521 --> 00:38:45,521
<i>[ Phone Beeps Off ]</i>             


542
00:38:47,459 --> 00:38:49,392
<i>[ Young Miss Parker ]</i>           
<i>MAMA!</i>                           


543
00:38:49,461 --> 00:38:51,761
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>NO. KEEP HER BACK. GO BACK.</i>     


544
00:38:51,830 --> 00:38:54,530
<i>[ Young Jarod ]</i>                 
<i>LEAVE ME ALONE!</i>                 
<i>[ Young Miss Parker ] MAMA!</i>     


545
00:39:05,577 --> 00:39:09,646
    YES. I'D LIKE TO PURCHASE   
    SOME TICKETS, PLEASE.       


546
00:39:58,129 --> 00:40:01,531
FROM THE SECRETARY.             
I'M IMPRESSED.                  


547
00:40:01,599 --> 00:40:03,199
            YOU SHOULD BE.      


548
00:40:05,603 --> 00:40:07,570
            HELL OF A DAY       
            FOR A DEPLOYMENT.   


549
00:40:07,639 --> 00:40:10,273
    - WHAT'S THE GOOD WORD?     
    - SURPRISE.                 


550
00:40:10,342 --> 00:40:12,708
YOUR KNACK FOR DISCIPLINE       
HAS INSPIRED ME.                


551
00:40:12,777 --> 00:40:16,746
I PUT TOGETHER                  
ONE LAST SURPRISE DRILL         
BEFORE WE DEPLOY. HERE.         


552
00:40:16,815 --> 00:40:19,148
<i>CRANK IT TO MAXIMUM.</i>            


553
00:40:19,217 --> 00:40:22,118
            THE JX-5 MAIN?      


554
00:40:22,187 --> 00:40:26,189
    THAT'LL OVERLOAD THE SYSTEM.
OH, RELAX.                      
I'VE SHUT OFF THE PRESSURE.     


555
00:40:26,257 --> 00:40:28,191
ONLY THE ALARM WILL SOUND.      


556
00:40:28,259 --> 00:40:31,594
THINK OF IT AS MY PERSONAL      
HIGHWAY TO HELL.                


557
00:40:42,140 --> 00:40:45,175
        WHAT'S JAROD WANTED FOR?
YOU NAME IT, HE'S DONE IT.      


558
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:52,381
    AFTER YOU.                  
<i>[ Whistling ]</i>                   


559
00:40:58,990 --> 00:41:02,959
        PRESSURE'S BUILDING UP. 
        HEY, WHERE THE HELL     
        IS EVERYBODY?           


560
00:41:03,028 --> 00:41:05,028
THEY'RE IN THE MESS.            


561
00:41:06,064 --> 00:41:07,997
WHICH IS SORT OF                
WHAT YOU'RE IN NOW.             


562
00:41:11,168 --> 00:41:13,936
<i>[ Alarm Blaring ]</i>               


563
00:41:17,509 --> 00:41:19,675
        HEY, O-OPEN THE HATCH!  


564
00:41:21,512 --> 00:41:24,547
<i>FORRESTER!</i>                      
<i>OPEN THE HATCH! NOW!</i>            


565
00:41:30,188 --> 00:41:31,854
<i>ARE YOU STARTING TO FEEL</i>        
<i>OUT OF IT?</i>                      


566
00:41:31,923 --> 00:41:34,157
    ARE YOU STARTING TO FEEL    
    DISORIENTED?                


567
00:41:34,225 --> 00:41:37,794
    - OPEN THE HATCH!           
    - I CAN'T DO THAT.          


568
00:41:37,863 --> 00:41:39,796
IT COULD BLOW                   
THE WHOLE SHIP UP.              


569
00:41:39,864 --> 00:41:42,565
        YOU'RE JUST             
        GOING TO HAVE TO DIE... 


570
00:41:42,634 --> 00:41:45,401
<i>TO SAVE EVERYBODY ELSE.</i>         


571
00:41:45,470 --> 00:41:47,636
    <i> JUST LIKE SCOTT SEAVER DID.</i>


572
00:41:48,639 --> 00:41:50,974
    IT'S A HORRIBLE WAY TO DIE. 


573
00:41:51,042 --> 00:41:53,642
    YOUR LUNGS,                 
    THEY FILL UP WITH TOXIC ICE,


574
00:41:53,711 --> 00:41:55,978
<i>AND THEN THEY FREEZE.</i>           


575
00:41:56,981 --> 00:41:58,914
<i>NO MATTER HOW HARD YOU TRY,</i>     


576
00:41:58,983 --> 00:42:01,951
YOU WON'T BE ABLE TO BREATHE.   


577
00:42:02,020 --> 00:42:05,788
    BUT THIS IS JUST            
    A JUDGMENT CALL             
    I'M GOING TO HAVE TO MAKE.  


578
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:09,058
    THINK OF IT AS              
    JUST ANOTHER DEMON          
    YOU HAVE TO DEAL WITH...    


579
00:42:09,127 --> 00:42:11,060
    WHEN YOU'RE AN OFFICER.     


580
00:42:11,129 --> 00:42:13,062
            HUH, NASHTON?       


581
00:42:13,131 --> 00:42:15,665
    OPEN THE HATCH!             
    THAT'S AN ORDER, COMMANDER! 


582
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:19,201
THAT'S AN ORDER                 
I CAN'T REALLY FOLLOW.          
YOU SEE,                        


583
00:42:19,270 --> 00:42:22,672
    I'M NOT AN OFFICER          
    ON THIS SHIP.               


584
00:42:22,741 --> 00:42:25,574
    THINK OF ME AS...           
    NAVAL INTELLIGENCE.         


585
00:42:25,643 --> 00:42:28,377
            YOU DON'T HAVE      
            ANYTHING ON ME!     


586
00:42:30,114 --> 00:42:32,381
<i>[ Jarod On Speaker ]</i>            
<i>I KNOW THAT YOU FORCED DANES...</i> 


587
00:42:32,450 --> 00:42:34,616
<i>TO TAMPER WITH THE EVIDENCE</i>     
<i>AFTER THE ACCIDENT,</i>             


588
00:42:34,685 --> 00:42:36,553
    TO RUIN SCOTT SEAVER'S NAME.


589
00:42:36,621 --> 00:42:39,622
<i>YOU HAD TO PRESERVE</i>             
<i>THE</i> MONROE<i> TO SAVE YOUR CAREER,</i> 


590
00:42:39,690 --> 00:42:41,790
<i>SO YOU LET</i>                      
<i>A 20-YEAR-OLD KID DIE!</i>          


591
00:42:41,859 --> 00:42:45,561
    DIDN'T YOU, NASHTON?        
    DIDN'T YOU? DIDN'T YOU?     
    DIDN'T YOU?                 


592
00:42:45,630 --> 00:42:48,030
                YES. YES.       


593
00:42:48,099 --> 00:42:50,032
            GOD, I'M SORRY.     


594
00:42:52,003 --> 00:42:54,003
<i>I LET HIM DIE.</i>                  


595
00:43:03,681 --> 00:43:05,815
            [ Gasping ]         


596
00:43:05,884 --> 00:43:09,285
    <i> NOW, DID YOU REALLY THINK</i>  
    <i> THAT I WOULD PUT</i>           
    <i> THIS SHIP INTO DANGER?</i>     


597
00:43:09,354 --> 00:43:11,587
<i>THAT WAS JUST LAUGHING GAS.</i>     


598
00:43:11,656 --> 00:43:14,256
    SO TRY TO LAUGH A LITTLE.   


599
00:43:14,325 --> 00:43:16,058
            [ Panting ]         


600
00:43:19,230 --> 00:43:22,164
TAKE HIM STRAIGHT TO            
CAPTAIN NAGEL.                  


601
00:43:22,233 --> 00:43:24,266
AND THAT'S AN ORDER.            


602
00:43:24,335 --> 00:43:26,902
                    YES, SIR.   


603
00:43:26,971 --> 00:43:29,138
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>DISMISSED.</i>                      


604
00:43:30,875 --> 00:43:34,978
    SIR, YOU HAVE A MAN         
    IMPERSONATING AN OFFICER    
    ON THIS SHIP.               


605
00:43:35,046 --> 00:43:37,446
            I KNOW THAT.        
            AT EASE, LIEUTENANT.
            THERE HE IS.        


606
00:43:42,254 --> 00:43:45,254
WE WERE TALKING ABOUT           
COMMANDER FORRESTER.            
                        JAROD?  


607
00:43:45,323 --> 00:43:47,256
<i>YES.</i>                            
    JAROD IS NAVAL INTELLIGENCE.


608
00:43:47,325 --> 00:43:49,625
    - I PLAN TO SEE TO IT       
      HE GETS A MEDAL.          
    - WHERE IS HE?              


609
00:43:49,694 --> 00:43:53,696
    WELL, HE WAS ORDERED        
    BACK TO NORFOLK             
    BY THE SECRETARY NO LESS.   


610
00:43:53,764 --> 00:43:56,365
    <i> IF YOU HURRY,</i>              
    <i> YOU MIGHT STILL CATCH HIM.</i> 


611
00:43:59,604 --> 00:44:01,437
<i>[ Horn Honks ]</i>                  


612
00:45:56,554 --> 00:46:01,957
    THE NEAREST OCEAN           
    IS 1,756 MILES FROM HERE.   


613
00:46:03,261 --> 00:46:05,560
THAT'S JUST THE WAY I LIKE IT.  


614
00:46:39,631 --> 00:46:40,629
            [ Mews ]            


